# Sonic Pi Syntax Reference

## Basic Building Blocks
- `use_bpm n` - Sets the global tempo in beats per minute
- `sleep n` - Pause for n beats
- `play :note` - Play a note (e.g., `:c4`, `:e3`, `:g5`)
- `sample :name` - Play a pre-recorded sound (e.g., `:bd_haus`, `:ambi_lunar_land`)

## Synths and Effects
- `use_synth :name` - Set the current synth (`:prophet`, `:fm`, `:tb303`, etc.)
- `with_fx :name do ... end` - Apply an effect to a block of code
- Common effects: `:reverb`, `:echo`, `:distortion`, `:slicer`

## Patterns and Loops
- `live_loop :name do ... end` - Create a continuously looping pattern
- `n.times do ... end` - Repeat a block of code n times
- `(ring ...)` - Create a ring buffer that loops continuously
- `tick`, `look` - Advance a counter or look at current value
- `chord(:c, :major)` - Create a chord (e.g., C major)
- `scale(:e, :minor_pentatonic)` - Create a scale (E minor pentatonic)

## Parameters
- `amp:` - Volume (typically 0-1)
- `pan:` - Stereo positioning (-1 to 1)
- `attack:`, `release:`, `sustain:` - Envelope parameters
- `cutoff:` - Filter cutoff frequency
- `rate:` - Sample playback rate
